<Base title="About" lang="en" alt="/about" description="About Tiago Vaccari and Vaccari's Code Podcast.">
  <article>
    <h1>About</h1>
    <p>Hi, I'm <strong>Tiago Vaccari</strong>, host of Vaccari's Code.</p>
    <p>
      I'm a Senior Software Engineer, currently leading AI initiatives and constantly exploring new
      technologies. I've worked in software development for over 20 years, across the Microsoft/.NET
      ecosystem, modern web development with TypeScript and React, and many other technologies along
      the way.
    </p>
    <p>
      I was born in Jundiaí, Brazil, lived in Bournemouth, in the UK, and in 2023 I moved to the
      United States. Today I live in Orlando, Florida. Outside of tech, I'm also a father, a
      cyclist, and someone who loves turning ideas into real projects.
    </p>
    <p>
      <strong>Vaccari's Code Podcast</strong> is one of those projects: an experiment in automating
      a media presence using AI. It tracks trends in software development and Artificial
      Intelligence, identifies the most relevant stories, and turns that content into blog posts,
      newsletters, and narrated podcast episodes.
    </p>
    <p>
      But it's not loose automation. Every piece of content goes through my own review before it's
      published, ensuring quality, context, and a human point of view. The narration even uses a
      clone of my own voice, creating a closer, more personal, and scalable experience.
    </p>
    <p>
      On Vaccari's Code, I share this journey across software, AI, automation, tech careers, and the
      behind-the-scenes of building digital products in practice.
    </p>
    <p>
      Find me on <a href="https://github.com/tvaccari34" rel="me">GitHub</a>, or
      <a href="/en/subscribe">subscribe to the newsletter</a>.
    </p>
  </article>
</Base>
